body:
```cmd
npm init --yes
npm install --save-dev hardhat
npm install --save
npx hardhat
❯ Create an empty hardhat.config.js
npm install --save @uniswap/v2-periphery @openzeppelin/contracts@3.4.1
npx hardhat compile
```
`Error HH411: The library @openzeppelin/contracts@3.4.1, imported from contracts/contract.sol, is not installed. Try installing it using npm.`

contracts/contract.sol
```
// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED

pragma solidity ^0.6.0;

import "@uniswap/v2-periphery/contracts/interfaces/IUniswapV2Router02.sol";
import "@uniswap/v2-periphery/contracts/interfaces/IERC20.sol";
import "@openzeppelin/contracts@3.4.1/access/AccessControl.sol"
```
```cmd
>mkdir contracts\@openzepplin
xcopy /E /I /H /C node_modules\@openzeppelin contracts\@openzepplin
```
Then edit contracts/contract.sol to:
```
// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED

pragma solidity ^0.6.0;

import "@uniswap/v2-periphery/contracts/interfaces/IUniswapV2Router02.sol";
import "@uniswap/v2-periphery/contracts/interfaces/IERC20.sol";
import "./@openzeppelin/contracts/access/AccessControl.sol";
```
Finally:
```cmd
npx hardhat compile
```
